Chief Executive Officer of Monimichelle, Ebi Egbe has assured that his company would deliver the best ever FIFA Goal Project in Ugborodo-Escarvos in Warri South local government area of Delta State. Egbe who accompanied NFF president Amaju Melvin Pinnick on a visit to the community early this week said the location of the project was fantastic as it would be nice to see football being played by the ocean. “We are going to deliver the best ever FIFA Goal Project. It will be the first of its kind amongst the Riverine communities in the Niger Delta,” Egbe said.  Meanwhile, the  former CAF Vice President had during the visit solicited for the cooperation of intimated the paramount ruler of Ugborodo community that world soccer governing body, FIFA has given approval for work to commence. On his part, the Paramount Ruler of Ugborodo community who spoke through the chairman of the interim community committee thanked FIFA and the NFF for the rare privilege and assured that all the necessary support will be provided for the actualization of the project.